  "content": "Next week water experts from across the world will descend on Stockholm for the annual World Water Week conference. To coincide with our coverage of the event, we've put together a list of influential voices on social media to keep you updated with the latest insights from the world of water. Have we missed someone? The list is not intended to be definitive, so add your suggestion in the comments thread below. @WorldBankWater The official feed of World Bank Water. Their account shares information on hydropower, sanitation and water supply issues. @EndWaterPoverty End Water Poverty is a global civil society coalition campaigning to end the water and sanitation crisis. @UN_Water UN-Water coordinates action around freshwater related issues, including sanitation. @UnescoIHE The UNESCO-IHE Institute for Water Education carries out educational, research and capacity development work relating to water. @UNICEFwater The Unicef account tweeting out news on the organisation's work on water, sanitation and hygiene. @Water Charity campaigning for \"safe water and the dignity of a toilet for all\". Their work focuses on financing, transparency and partnership in the water sector. @CatarinadeAlbuq Catarinade Albuquerqu is the UN special rapporteur for the human rights to water and sanitation. @Alex_Verbeek Alex is a Yale World Fellow and Dutch diplomat with an interest in the relationship between energy, water and food. @WaterAidUK One of the biggest actors in the water world, WaterAid is an international charity working on sanitation and improving access to safe water. @WASHfunders Wash Funders describes itself as a \"one stop shop\" for funding and data for donors and policymakers interested in water, sanitation, and hygiene. Read more stories like this: \u2022 'We need to talk about open defecation' \u2022 World Water Day: are filters the future? \u2022 Investing in sustainable water systems: who is leading the way? Join our community of development professionals and humanitarians. Follow @GuardianGDP on Twitter.",
